ww.spin.com/featured/best-albums-2018/|title=51 Best Albums of 2018: Staff Picks|date=2018-12-12|website=Spin|access-date=2019-11-17}}</ref>}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | ''[[Stereogum]]''\n| The 50 Best Albums of 2018\n| {{center|3}}\n| {{center|<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gray |first1=Julia |title=The 50 Best Albums Of 2018 |url=https://www.stereogum.com/featured/the-best-albums-of-2018/ |website=Stereogum |accessdate=December 8, 2018 |date=December 4, 2018}}</ref>}}\n|-\n|The 100 Best Albums Of The 2010s\n| {{center|42}}\n| {{center|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stereogum.com/featured/best-albums-of-the-2010s-list/|title=The 100 Best Albums Of The 2010s|date=2019-11-04|website=Stereogum|access-date=2019-11-12}}</ref>}}\n|-\n|''[[Thrillist]]''\n| The Best Albums of 2018\n| {{center|22}}\n| {{center|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thrillist.com/entertainment/nation/best-albums-of-2018|title=The Best Albums of 2018|last=Jackson|first=Dan|date=2019-02-11|website=Thrillist|access-date=2019-11-17}}</ref>}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | ''[[Uproxx]]''\n| The 50 Best Albums of 2018\n| {{center|5}}\n| {{center|<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gilke |first1=Chloe |title=The 50 Best Albums Of 2018 |url=https://uproxx.com/music/best-albums-of-2018-ranked/ |website=Uproxx |accessdate=December 8, 2018 |date=December 3, 2018}}</ref>}}\n|-\n| The Best Albums Of The 2010s\n| {{center|68}}\n| {{center|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://uproxx.com/music/best-albums-2010s-ranked-decade/|title=The 100 Best Albums Of The 2010s, Ranked|date=2019-10-07|website=UPROXX|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-20}}</ref>}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]''\n| 20 Best Albums of 2018\n| {{center|7}}\n| {{center|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/music/opinion/chris-willman-20-best-albums-2018-elvis-costello-brandi-carlile-pistol-annies-1203089293/|title=Chris Willman\u2019s 20 Best Albums of 2018|last=Willman|first=Chris|last2=Willman|first2=Chris|date=2018-12-14|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2019-12-20}}</ref>}}\n|-\n| The Best Albums of the Decade\n| {{center|-}}\n| {{center|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/feature/best-albums-decade-2010-2019-1203444452/|title=The Best Albums of the Decade|last=Willman|first=Andrew Barker,Jem Aswad,Chris|last2=Barker|first2=Andrew|date=2019-12-20|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2019-12-20|last3=Aswad|first3=Jem|last4=Willman|first4=Chris}}</ref>}}\n|}\n\n==Commercial performance==\nIn the United States, ''Sweetener'' debuted at number one on the US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] with 231,000 [[album-equivalent unit]]s, of which 127,000 were from traditional album sales, thus becoming Grande's third number-one album in the United States. It also logged the largest streaming week for a non-hip hop album by a female artist; the songs were streamed 126.7 million times in the album's first week.<ref name=\"BB200\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8472196/ariana-grande-sweetener-number-one-billboard-200-chart|title=Ariana Grande Earns Third No. 1 Album on Billboard 200 Chart With 'Sweetener'|work=Billboard|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|date=August 26, 2018|accessdate=August 27, 2018}}</ref> On the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] chart issue dated September 1, ten songs (nine of which are from ''Sweetener'') appeared simultaneously, placing Grande as the fourth female artist with the most simultaneous entries on the chart by a solo female artist behind [[Taylor Swift]], [[Beyonc\u00e9]], and [[Cardi B]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8472538/ariana-grande-10th-top-10-hit-10-songs-billboard-hot-100-chart|title=Ariana Grande Earns 10th Top 10 Hit, Lands 10 Songs on Billboard Hot 100|work=Billboard|last=Zellner|first=Xander|date=August 27, 2018|accessdate=August 29, 2018}}</ref> Grande also topped the [[List of number-one artists on the Billboard Artist 100|Artist 100]] chart the same week due to album sales and song streams.<ref name=\"artist100\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8472655/ariana-grande-returns-to-no-1-artist-100-chart|title=Ariana Grande Returns to No. 1 On the Artist 100 Chart, Aretha Franklin Reaches No. 2|date=August 28, 2018|accessdate=September 30, 2018|first=Xander|last=Zellner|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref> In its second week, ''Sweetener'' dropped to number four moving 75,000 equivalent album units,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Caulfield|first1=Keith|title=BTS Scores Second No. 1 Album on Billboard 200 Chart With 'Love Yourself: Answer'|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8473245/bts-love-yourself-answer-album-debuts-No1-billboard-200-chart|accessdate=September 2, 2018|work=Billboard|date=September 2, 2018}}</ref> while in its third week, it fell one position to number five moving an additional 56,000 equivalent album units.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Caulfield|first1=Keith|title=Eminem Earns Ninth No. 1 Album on Billboard 200 Chart With 'Kamikaze'|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8474185/eminem-kamikaze-debuts-number-one-billboard-200-chart|accessdate=September 9, 2018|work=Billboard|date=September 9, 2018}}</ref> The album was ranked 38th on the 2018 year-end ''Billboard'' 200 chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2018/top-billboard-200-albums|title=Billboard 2018 Year End Charts|website=Billboard}}</ref> On April 3, 2019, the album was certified [[RIAA Certification|platinum]] by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA) for combined sales and album-equivalent units of over a million units in the United States.<ref>[https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=default-award&ar=ariana+grande&ti=&lab=&genre=&format=&date_option=release&from=&to=&award=&type=&category=&adv=SEARCH#search_section]</ref>\n\nIn the United Kingdom, ''Sweetener'' debuted at number one on the [[UK Albums Chart]], moving 45,000 album-equivalent units.<ref>http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/ariana-grandes-sweetener-earns-her-a-second-number-1-on-the-official-albums-chart-im-so-grateful-__23727/</ref> It became her second number-one album in the UK, and her fastest selling album to date.<ref>http://www.mtv.co.uk/ariana-grande/news/ariana-grande-sweetener-uk-album-chart-number-1</ref> Following its release, two album tracks entered the [[UK Singles Chart]] as \"[[Breathin]]\" debuted at number 8, and \"Sweetener\" landed at number 22, while the single \"God Is a Woman\" ascended six places to number 6.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/charts/singles-chart/20180824/7501/|title=Official Singles Chart Top 100: 24 August 2018 \u2013 30 August 2018|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=August 25, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn Australia, the album became Grande's third number one on the [[ARIA Charts|ARIA Albums Chart]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ariacharts.com.au/news/2018/sweetener-lands-ariana-grande-third-1-album|title=Sweetener lands Ariana Grande third #1 album|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]]|date=August 25, 2018|accessdate=August 25, 2018}}</ref> with all 15 of its tracks placing on the ARIA Singles Chart in the same week.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.auspop.com.au/2018/8/aria-chart-watch-487/|title=ARIA Chart Watch #487|publisher=auspOp|date=August 25, 2018|accessdate=August 25, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Legacy ==\nIn December 2018, [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] placed ''Sweetener'' at the top their year end list for the best albums of 2018. Complimenting Grande's take on sadness, they said \"she didn\u2019t let her past define her, and she didn\u2019t dwell on what her future may hold, either\" and  praised Grande that \"while most fans couldn\u2019t possibly relate to her extraordinary circumstances, Grande still ended the year seeming more approachable and human than ever\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/photos/8489227/best-albums-2018-staff-picks|title=50 Best Albums of 2018: Staff Picks|date=2018-12-10|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref> ''Sweetener'' alongside its followup ''[[Thank U, Next]]'' placed on Billboard' decade end album's list \"The 100 Greatest Albums the 2010s\" at numbers 38 and 8 respectively. They called ''Sweetener'' her most personal sound and \"a radiant, pure snapshot of what stumbling upon happiness sounds like\". They said that Grande had \"found herself -- and graduated to a new level of pop superstardom\".\n\n[[Paper (magazine)|Paper magazine]] placed the closing track of the album \"[[Get Well Soon (song)|''Get Well Soon'']]\" at number 15 on their \"PAPER's Top 100 Songs of 2018\" list naming it \"waltzing, lyrically superb\" and praising the album saying that Grande \"transformed her pain into something digestible, like sweetener molecules settling into a bitter cup of coffee;. The article pointed out the album's parallelism with [[Beyonc\u00e9]]'s 2016 album, \"[[Lemonade (Beyonc\u00e9 album)|''Lemonade'']]\", saying \"like Beyonc\u00e9 who made ''Lemonade'' from her own life's lemons just two years ago, ''Sweetener''<nowiki/>'s legacy will be its resoundingly positive message about true love's grace and its ability to help us cope with loss.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.papermag.com/paper-top-100-songs-2018-2623667609.html?rebelltitem=132#rebelltitem132?rebelltitem=132|title=2018 Top 100 Songs|date=2018-12-21|website=PAPER|language=en|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref> Sweetener also landed a number 2 position on their \"PAPER's Top 20 Albums of 2018\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.papermag.com/top-25-albums-2018-2623655747.html?rebelltitem=104#rebelltitem104?rebelltitem=104|title=PAPER's Top 20 Albums of 2018|date=2018-12-17|website=PAPER|language=en|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\nCredits adapted from the album's [[liner notes]].<ref name=\"LinerNotes\"/>\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Standard edition<ref name=\"LinerNotes\